ShareOverviewSummarySouth Jersey Gas Company has worked on fourteen contracts worth $4.26 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2016), the organization received a total of $189,000 USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Justice and General Services Administration.

